{
  "texts": [
    "This lack of parallelisation leads to a performance bottleneck.",
    "Further, the basic architecture described here follows the Markov property: each state is assumed to be dependent only on the previously seen state.",
    "This can lead to problems processing sequences with long-range dependencies and is the reason why LSTMs and GRUs are useful.",
    "The drawbacks of RNNs are mitigated by the transformer architecture proposed by Vaswani et al. (2017).",
    "Since their introduction, transformer-based architectures have quickly become dominant for achieving state-of-the-art results on many NLP tasks."
  ]
}